article.headline: Taylor has 26 in Georgia State's 82-79 victory over Marshall
article.description: — Lucas Taylor scored 26 points and his layup with 10 seconds left sealed Georgia State's 82-79 win over Marshall on Friday night.
article.linkText: Taylor has 26 in Georgia State's 82-79 victory over Marshall

article.story: ATLANTA -- — Lucas Taylor scored 26 points and his layup with 10 seconds left sealed Georgia State's 82-79 win over Marshall on Friday night. Taylor shot 10 for 16 (3 for 5 from 3-point range) and 3 of 5 from the free throw line for the Panthers (14-16, 8-10 Sun Belt Conference). Toneari Lane scored 16 points, shooting 7 for 13, including 2 for 6 from beyond the arc. Dwon Odom finished 6 of 11 from the floor to finish with 13 points, while adding seven rebounds and 10 assists. Kevon Voyles led the way for the Thundering Herd (12-19, 7-11) with 23 points, six assists and two steals. Nate Martin added 16 points and 11 rebounds for Marshall. Obinna Anochili-Killen also put up 16 points, seven rebounds and three steals. The loss is the seventh straight for the Thundering Herd. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
